  "text": "The dopamine D 2 R has been classically shown to mediate its modulatory effects on synaptic transmission via signal transduction through G i/o -mediated inhibition of cAMP [CITATION_1] . In addition to this G protein-dependent pathway, several lines of evidence suggest that D 2 R can also engage a G protein-independent pathway, inhibiting the Akt/GSK-3 signaling cascade. This mode of signaling is mediated by a molecular complex involving the D 2 R,â-arrestin 2, Akt, and the multimeric protein phosphatase PP2A [CITATION_2] .",
